{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"lang","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/lang","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div style=\"background:#f5f5f5; margin: 5px 0;\" id=\"sect1\">\n    <b><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Transforming_XML_with_XSLT/The_Netscape_XSLT_XPath_Reference\">XSLT/XPath Reference</a></b>: <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XSLT/Element\">XSLT elements</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/EXSLT\">EXSLT functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions\">XPath functions</a>, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Axes\">XPath axes</a>\n</div>\n<p>The <code>lang</code> function determines whether the context node matches the given language and returns boolean true or false.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":true,"content":"<pre class=\"notranslate\">lang(string )\n</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"arguments","title":"Arguments","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"string\"><code>string</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The language code or localization (language and country) code to be matched.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"returns","title":"Returns","isH3":true,"content":"<p><code>true</code> if the context node matches the given languages. Otherwise, <code>false</code>.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes","title":"Notes","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n  <li>A node's language is determined by its <code>xml:lang</code> attribute. If the current node does not have an <code>xml:lang</code> attribute, then the value of the <code>xml:lang</code> attribute of the nearest ancestor that has an <code>xml:lang</code> attribute will determine the current node's language. If the language cannot be determined (no ancestor has an <code>xml:lang</code> attribute), this function will return false.</li>\n  <li>If the given <code>string</code> does not specify a country code, this function will match nodes of that language with any country code. The converse is not true.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Given this fragment of XML:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: xml notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">xml:</span>lang</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>en<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>I went up a floor.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">xml:</span>lang</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>en-GB<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>I took the lift.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>p</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\"><span class=\"token namespace\">xml:</span>lang</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>en-US<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>I rode the elevator.<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>p</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And this part of an XSL template:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: xml notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token namespace\">xsl:</span>value-of</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">select</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>count(//p[lang(<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>en<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>)])<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token namespace\">xsl:</span>value-of</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">select</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>count(//p[lang(<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>en-GB<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>)])<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token namespace\">xsl:</span>value-of</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">select</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>count(//p[lang(<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>en-US<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>)])<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token namespace\">xsl:</span>value-of</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">select</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>count(//p[lang(<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>de<span class=\"token punctuation\">'</span>)])<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The output might be:</p>\n<pre class=\"notranslate\">3\n1\n1\n0\n</pre>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"defined","title":"Defined","isH3":true,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/1999/REC-xpath-19991116/#function-lang\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">XPath 1.0 4.3</a></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"gecko_support","title":"Gecko support","isH3":true,"content":"<p>Supported.</p>"}}],"toc":[],"summary":"The lang function determines whether the context node matches the given language and returns boolean true or false.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-09T05:38:45.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"lang","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"lang","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"lang","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/xpath/functions/lang","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/xpath/functions/lang/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/f22e42182591e38590c9add80de91a51bce3cde2","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath","title":"XPath"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions","title":"Functions"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/XPath/Functions/lang","title":"lang"}],"pageTitle":"lang - XPath | MDN","noIndexing":false}}